Though the shrine grounds are modest at 24 tsubo, it is surrounded by several notable [[black pine]] (クロマツ) trees, designated as one of the "Ten Famous Trees of Funabashi." The shrine is located along [[National Route 14]], a route historically known as the [[Narita Highway]], frequented by pilgrims to [[Naritasan Shinshoji Temple]] and travelers along the [[Sakura Highway]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.midori-kikin.or.jp/tree/main4.html|title=Katsushika Shrine Black Pine Trees|publisher=Funabashi City Green Fund|accessdate=2009-04-12}}</ref>

